-- Afgri, Nedbank, Johan Daniel, Telkom May Move: South Africa Stock Preview
-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 2010-10-15T05:56:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/afgri-nedbank-johan-daniel-telkom-may-move-south-africa-stock-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  declined
16.12, or 0.1 percent, to 30,251.34 at the 5 p.m. close
yesterday.  Afgri Ltd.  (AFR SJ): The company that handles about a third
of the grain produced in South Africa holds its annual general
meeting. Afgri declined 8 cents, or 1.2 percent, to 6.70 rand.  John Daniel Holdings Ltd.  (JDH SJ): The venture capital
investment company said its loss widened to 6.7 million rand
from 4.5 million rand in the year through June 30. The stock
fell 2 cents, or 18 percent, to 9 cents.  Nedbank Group Ltd.  (NED SJ): HSBC Holdings Plc is close to
pulling out of a deal to acquire a stake in South Africa’s
fourth-largest bank from Old Mutual Plc (OML SJ), the Financial
Times reported, citing people close to the matter that it didn’t
identify. HSBC spokesman Adrian Russell declined to comment on
the report. Nedbank spokesman Don Bowden declined to comment.
Nedbank fell 2.20 rand, or 1.5 percent, to 146.80 rand.  Northam Platinum Ltd.  (NHM SJ): Workers at the platinum
producer’s only mine, Zondereinde, may decide on the company’s
latest pay offer. The mine has been shut since Sept. 5 when the
workers started a strike over pay. The stock retreated 20 cents,
or 0.4 percent, to 46.89 rand.  Telkom South Africa Ltd.  (TKG SJ): Africa’s largest fixed-
line operator said it plans to start offering post-paid mobile-
phone services in South Africa from next month. The stock fell
15 cents, or 0.4 percent, to 37.40 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) fell 0.2 percent to $22.79.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) slid 1.4 percent to $47.45. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) gained 0.5 percent to $70.24. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) declined 0.7 percent to $5.35. Gold Fields Ltd.
(GFI US) fell 1.7 percent to $15.89. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) lost 0.3 percent to $11.39. Impala Platinum Holdings
Co. (IMPUY US) rose 1 percent to $28.64. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
rose 0.2 percent to $5.12. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) fell 0.8 percent
to $46.38.  To contact the reporter on this story:
